Key Match Events: Chris Bassitt struck out nine batters, matching his season-high.
Brayan Bello threw a career-high eight innings, allowing just two hits and one walk while striking out nine.

Post-Match Reflections: Chris Bassitt credited his success to switching his spot on the mound from the first base side to the third base side.
John Schneider praised Bassitt's mix of pitches and his ability to locate fastballs.
Alex Cora admired Bassitt's pitching strategy and execution.
